title: For Sale/Trade:  AK-47 PISTOL, ZASTAVA M-92 PAP CUSTOM WITH 25 MAGS AND 1800 ROUNDS
location: Northeast of Denver, Colorado, United States
postcontent:
I am selling a new Zastava M-92 PAP AK-47 custom pistol with 25 new magazine's and 1750 rounds of ammo. All numbers match.  I own a number of AK-47s, both rifles and pistols. I did extensive homework and research on each and every AK I own prior to purchasing them. This pistol was by far the one I looked into the most. I owed two Draco Romanian and had very little knowledge of the Zastava M-92. It did not take long to realize this pistol was a quality machine with outstanding reviews. After looking at one in person it was quite obvious that it was a far superior AK pistol than my Draco and most of my AKs. My Arsenal is the only one compatible.  Most AKs tend to fit loose and sloppy with little attention to detail. This Zastava M-92 is perfectly fitted and tight everywhere. The only complaint with them is the furniture comes very plain with no finish and often dirty which as you can see I paid a nice chunk to have mine totally refinished in Russian Red. Zastava is Serbian and considered to be one of the best AK makers if not the best period. All their products are quality and the M 92 pistols are made new in Serbia. She has had two 30 round mags ran through her the day I got her. Unbelievable performance and extremely accurate. The following day I had her torn down and rebuilt.
The Zastava PAP M-92 was taken all the way down and each part was surprisingly well finished but not good enough for me. Each piece and component was hand worked and polished, then washed in an acid solution to remove all micro shavings.  Rivets replaced with a much more superior rivet. The furniture was taken all the way down and redone in Russian Red Wood and a built proof clear coat given for an amazingly tough and beautiful finish.  The pistol grip was coated in a rubberized coating for exceptional gripping as was one of the new TapCo mags.  She comes with 24 new 30 round magazines and one 40 round mag for 25 total. 15 of those are new or restored high quality Easter Block steel mags. There are a few very rare Romanian mags from 1964 that have been restored like new. The other 10 are a variation of new TapCo 30 round mags.  She comes with just over 1800 rounds of quality and fresh 7.62x39 ammo some of that can be seen in the photos. I have a few mags loaded with very high end penetration hollow points.  All mags in the photos are full for a total of just over 1700 rounds total.
If you just want an AK then this might not be the one for you. If you are looking for the perfect AK performance and cosmetically as well as superior quality then this is something worth looking into. She is a beautiful beast!

Thank you for taking the time to look. Serious buyers interested in a quality custom AK only please.

title: For Sale:  Petition to Defend Our Gun Rights - Send to Your Elected Representatives
postcontent:
Petition To
The United States Congress
The President of the United States
The United States Supreme Court


Whereas, the Bill of Rights added further declaratory and restrictive clauses to the U.S. Constitution in order to prevent misconstruction or abuse of its powers; and

Whereas, those further declaratory and restrictive clauses relate directly to the fundamental rights of individuals, including the sweeping declaratory Ninth and Tenth Amendments, which guarantee that powers not delegated by the people to the United States in the Constitution and those powers not granted to the separate states were reserved to the people; and

Whereas, history demonstrates convincingly that the first act of tyrannical governments in expanding their powers beyond those granted to them is to disarm or short arm individuals so as to render them defenseless against the states heavily armed police and soldiery; and

Whereas, the authors of the first ten amendments included the Second Amendment in the Bill of Rights because they understood this lesson of history and consequently believed as a matter of fact that a well-armed citizenry is both a necessary condition of liberty and the only effective deterrent against tyranny; and

Whereas, there is a plethora of evidence confirming these facts in the writings and statements of the Foundersincluding the author of the Declaration of Independence, Thomas Jefferson, and the Father of the Constitution, James Madison, as well as in numerous other documents and writings contemporary of the Founding of the United States; and

Whereas, these writings and statements also demonstrate conclusively that the authors of the U.S. Constitution and the Bill of Rights believed as a matter of philosophy that every human being possesses an inalienable, fundamental, natural right, which pre-dates the Second Amendment, to own and bear arms and, if necessary, to use those arms in self defense, including self defense against tyrannical government agents, police forces and armies that would over step their proper bounds; and

Whereas, George Mason, the Father of the Bill of Rights, summed it up best when he said, To disarm the people is the best and most effectual way to enslave them; and

Whereas, the Second Amendment was designed specifically to prevent the peoples enslavement by guaranteeing that individuals not only would retain the right and means to defend themselves against private outlaws who would do them harm but also to provide individuals an effective deterrent against and a means to defend themselves against tyrannical and oppressive governments and their agents acting improperly under the color of law; and 

Whereas, the Second Amendment was and remains an unambiguous and unrestricted, sweeping guarantee of individuals right to own and bear arms and use them in their own self defense; now

Therefore, We the Undersigned petition the United States Government to cease and desist all efforts to disarm or short-arm the American people by limiting and disparaging the Second Amendment or rendering it a dead letter through federal legislation, interpretation and regulation.
